    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">431 Stevens <choice><abbr>st.</abbr><expan>street</expan></choice><ptr target="prc.00048_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1877-06-14" rend="right">June 14&#8212;11 a m<ptr target="prc.00048_n2"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend</salute>
            </opener>
            
            <p>I am afraid to venture out much in the heat of the day (as part of my trouble of the head is <hi rend="italic">sun affection, &amp; susceptibility</hi>)&#8212;so I give up the <hi rend="italic">Congress</hi> visit <hi rend="italic"><choice><orig>to-day</orig><reg>today</reg></choice></hi>.</p>
            
            <p>We will see about it, either <hi rend="italic">next Wednesday</hi>, or indeed most any other (cloudy) day&#8212;as I want to go aboard&#8212;&amp; you shall go, if you wish to. Love to mother, father &amp; Jack.<ptr target="prc.00048_n3"/></p>
            
            <closer>         
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
